Here is the cleaned up text:

OmniStudio FlexCards supports versioning. You can create an identical copy of a FlexCard by creating a new version and keeping other versions with the same name, and author, but with a new version number.

The name, author, and version combination must be unique for each component in an org. Only one version of a component can be active at a time.

When you create a new version of a FlexCard, the version number increases by 1 and the Status is inactive.

You can't choose the author or name of the new version when creating a new FlexCard based on a current FlexCard. To update the Author and/or Name, you must clone your FlexCard.

The following fields are involved in the versioning process:

* Name: specifies the user organization that created the FlexCard
* Author: indicates the team creating the content
* Version: increases by one with every new version
* Active: indicates whether a record is active for run time use

Create a New Version of a FlexCard when you want to make slight modifications to a current FlexCard. Creating a version makes an exact copy with a version number equal to the latest version number plus one.
